th west of Hallowshade Moor. There are a lot of them, I had more than 20 on track. I'm not sure about their lvl and if they group up as they conned green to us, guess they are around 30, someone told they can summon and hit sometimes close to 100. We killed about 70 of them to get 2 perfect owlbear pelts.<br><br>Shadeling silks are dropped in Shadeweaver's Thicket in the east of the zone from Silkworms (south east area) and Shades (north east area). Shades are looking like Skels. Maybe you can buy the silks from newbies.<br><br>The pattern is a mini quest. Kill the Grimling Runner in Tenebrous Mountains. He spawns at the entrance to Grimling Forest. I've been told he's a 90 minutes spawn. He appears and starts walking west. Was an easy kill for us, around 1000 HP. He drops an item looking like a bag, but isn't a bag, you can store it in a backpack, lore and no drop. Then head to Katta Castellum and find Rallic Aristos. Zoning in from Tenebrous Mountains you find him in the first large building to your right. If you enter the building head three times left, he is standing in a small room there. Hail him and turn in the Grimling Runner's bag for the pattern after some conversation. The pattern is lore, but tradeable.<br><br>Duvinya<br>Wanderer lvl 54<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub20.ezboard.com/udaanidreamcatcher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daani Dreamcatcher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>wanna be evil druid</span><br>  Posts: 190<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/7/02 8:25:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub20.ezboard.com/fbloodsongfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=105.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rallic Pack</span><hr size=1> Duvinya... I just wanted to let you know, I followed your directions for this quest.. it was easy to follow and didn't take much time to complete =) 